explains: adj. 不成文的；口头的；没有记录的
wordGroup: unwritten law [律]习惯法；[律]不成文法

sentences.en: Without unwritten rules civilized life would be impossible.
sentences.cn: 没有不成文的规章，就不会有文明生活。

sentences.en: They obey the one unwritten rule that binds them all–no talking.
sentences.cn: 他们遵守那条约束他们所有人的不成文规定—不许说话。

sentences.en: The photographs were to be included in his as yet unwritten autobiography.
sentences.cn: 这些照片准备要收入他那尚未写的自传。
